<br>
Not really, rangers do significantly more damage with bows than warriors do.  Hits for 100+ are common.  They also not only have the chance to critical, but 51+ they also start getting what is known as &quot;double damage&quot; hits.  They actually get a message saying that their shot did double damage.  When they crit on top of a double damage hit, look out.  The best I've seen first hand from a ranger friend using a Bow of the Huntsmen (the 20/30 81DD proc bow someone else was talking about earlier) was a 618 double hit critical.  And that's not even from an uber ranger using a massive bow.<br>
<br>
They can also throw in their Trueshot discipline (level 55+) when it's available, making all hits double damage hits for 2 minutes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaabidano.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aabidano</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/4/02 6:16:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2157.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: moo</span><hr size=1> I've got a compound shadewood, 200(I think) range.  With 125 range arrows it's great for pulling.  I can usually get a few of more shots off as the critter is coming in, adding a bit to agro.<br>
