I hit RM in the early AM's to farm cash for myself or guild funds, and I love grabbing HG out from under the noses of the 60 druids that kite 1200 of em around the hill(/sarcasm).  Or, pulling in ME on an exp grind.  Sometimes, I don't even have to move very far from my group, take a few steps, and *twang* pulled an ape/xi or whatever.<br>
I personlly love using my bow.  High crit so far is 147.  My ranger friends are always making fun of me when I stand at the back of a raid with them and shoot arrows for a few (when not MT of course, and on relaxed raids like HoT or something).  And, when you have some time to kill, ie waiting for Nexus portals, is a good time to work on arrow crafting.<br>
